Today it hit me, like a brick. Of all the time we’ve spent here in my home land, it hit me the most today. As I walked through the cemetery, full of those who used to breathe life into this land, how is it that we honour them? Those who came before us, the  inheritance they’ve left for us, the life they’ve built as our foundation, the traditions they’ve kept so that we may have a place to belong to. And today, more than ever, I’m determined to continue this journey to find out who I am because of them. Don’t forget your elders. And if you don’t know who they are yet, then seek them. Find out. 🏔
Thank you @taylorwitiw for being with me through this journey and putting up with my endless crying. .

✥ Chasing pigeons ✥ I’ve also been chasing a lot of other things lately, in hopes of discovering who I really am, what I really like. My grandma, who has dementia, in a moment of clarity asked me ‘do you remember where you come from? Do you remember your roots, the roads you’ve walked?’ In trying to find myself I’ve discovered that instead of chasing things in front of me, I need to chase what/who has always been behind me - my culture, my ancestors, their way of doing, being, and seeing the world. ✥ 𝚆𝚑𝚊𝚝 𝚑𝚊𝚟𝚎 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚋𝚎𝚎𝚗 𝚌𝚑𝚊𝚜𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚕𝚊𝚝𝚎𝚕𝚢? ✥

This year has been full of amazing experiences and tremendous challenges and I am grateful for each and every one of them ❈ Having gone through culture shock when I first moved here, losing myself for a bit, trying to figure out what it means to live in Canada and to live as me, and now being on the other side of these questions, I can say that I could not have done it on my own ❈ I am so grateful and honoured to have an unwavering, loving partner by my side, amazing family (🇷🇴on both continents 🇨🇦), and wonderful friends. This year has allowed me to get to know and discover myself, a journey that was both very challenging and tremendously rewarding ❈ I am thrilled to walk into a new year a better me, awaiting and hopeful of the new challenges to come ❈ "The best thing one can do when it's raining is to let it rain" ~Longfellow ❈ I am ready for you #2019! ❈ Happy New Year everyone 🥂🍾🎊
